OL,3,CCaptain of ship involved in fatal
OL,4,Ccrash denies falling asleep
OL,6,FThe captain of a ship which crashed
OL,7,Finto a tanker killing a crewman has
OL,8,Fdenied falling asleep or leaving his
OL,9,Fpost.
OL,11,FRussian Vladimir Motin, 59, was on
OL,12,Fsole watch duty when the Solong
OL,13,Fcollided with the anchored Stena
OL,14,FImmaculate near the Humber Estuary
OL,15,Flast March.
OL,17,FFilipino national Mark Angelo Pernia,
OL,18,F38, died in the incident.
OL,20,FMotin is on trial at the Old Bailey
OL,21,Faccused of Mr Pernia's manslaughter.
